    <!-- Themed-icon (Android 13+) silhouette. The system tints this with
         the user's chosen monochrome theme colour, so detail must live in
         the alpha channel: the filled star region reads as the silhouette,
         the closed C subpath punches through as transparent via
         android:fillType="evenOdd".

         Star geometry matches `ic_launcher_foreground.xml`. The C here is
         a closed crescent (outer arc R=11, inner arc R=7) rather than a
         stroked path — closed-path is the only way to get a true hole
         through the silhouette under evenOdd. Sharp corners at the
         opening instead of the foreground's rounded caps; acceptable
         loss of fidelity for the monochrome rendering. -->
